items.title: Trump hits Russian oil companies with long-threatened sanctions: 'It was time'
items.description: The Treasury Department said new economic penalties will target Russia’s two largest oil companies, Rosneft and Lukoil, as well as their subsidiaries.

items.title: Entire East Wing expected to be demolished as soon as this weekend: Sources
items.description: The White House is expected to demolish the entire East Wing to allow for construction of President Trump’s ballroom, sources familiar with the projec...

items.title: Mom arrested after leaving baby girl at New York subway station
items.description: The mother of a newborn baby found at a Midtown Manhattan subway station has been taken into custody in Queens, law enforcement sources said.

items.title: WATCH:  Parkinson's disease patient plays clarinet during brain surgery
items.description: A patient undergoing brain surgery plays the clarinet, allowing surgeons to instantly hear the impacts of the treatment.

items.title: WATCH:  Parents of Israeli hostage killed by Hamas waiting for his body to be returned
items.description: Omer Neutra from New York state is one of two deceased American Israeli hostages whose bodies have still not been returned by Hamas.
